The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, March 28, 2004 				 Jilted youth held for rape
 A STAFF REPORTER																								A 21-year-old youth allegedly raped a teenaged co-worker who had been resisting his advances. 																								Ramjan Ali was arrested on Friday from a tailoring shop in the Karaya police station area on charges of raping an 18-year-old girl who worked with him. Police said Ali was remanded in custody till April 2.																								Police said the girl had been recruited a few months ago by an NGO. Ali had proposed to her several times but had been turned down.																								On Thursday night, Ali crept into her house and proposed to her again. When he faced another refusal, he raped her. On Friday, the girl reported the incident to an NGO activist who brought her to us, an officer added.
